ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: What is your living situation today?
Notes: 1= I have a steady place to live; 2= I have a place to live today, but I am worried about losing it in the future; 3= I do not have a steady place to live (I am temporarily staying with others, in a hotel, in a shelter, living outside on the street, on a beach, in a car, abandoned building, bus or train station, or in a park)

ElementDescription: Think about the place you live. Do you have problems with any of the following: Pests such as bugs, ants, or mice
Notes: 0= Unchecked; 1= Checked

ElementDescription: Think about the place you live. Do you have problems with any of the following: Mold
Notes: 0= Unchecked; 1= Checked

ElementDescription: Think about the place you live. Do you have problems with any of the following: Lead paint or pipes
Notes: 0= Unchecked; 1= Checked

ElementDescription: Think about the place you live. Do you have problems with any of the following: Lack of heat
Notes: 0= Unchecked; 1= Checked

ElementDescription: Think about the place you live. Do you have problems with any of the following: Oven or stove not working
Notes: 0= Unchecked; 1= Checked

ElementDescription: Think about the place you live. Do you have problems with any of the following: Smoke detectors missing or not working
Notes: 0= Unchecked; 1= Checked

ElementDescription: Think about the place you live. Do you have problems with any of the following: Water leaks
Notes: 0= Unchecked; 1= Checked

ElementDescription: Think about the place you live. Do you have problems with any of the following: None of the above
Notes: 0= Unchecked; 1= Checked

ElementDescription: Within the past 12 months, how often were you worried whether food would run out before you got money to buy more?
Notes: 1 = Most of the time; 2 = Sometimes; 3 = Never; 777=Not applicable

ElementDescription: Within the past 12 months, how often did the food not last and you didn't have money to get more?
Notes: 1 = Most of the time; 2 = Sometimes; 3 = Never; 777=Not applicable

ElementDescription: In the past 12 months, has lack of reliable transportation kept you from medical appointments, meetings, work or from getting things needed for daily living?
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes

ElementDescription: In the past 12 months has the electric, gas, oil, or water company threatened to shut off services in your home?
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes; 2= Already Shut off

ElementDescription: How often does anyone, including family and friends, physically hurt you?
Notes: 1= Never; 2= Rarely; 3= Sometimes; 4= Fairly Often; 5= Frequently

ElementDescription: How often does anyone, including family and friends, insult or talk down to you?
Notes: 1= Never; 2= Rarely; 3= Sometimes; 4= Fairly Often; 5= Frequently

ElementDescription: How often does anyone, including family and friends, threaten you with harm?
Notes: 1= Never; 2= Rarely; 3= Sometimes; 4= Fairly Often; 5= Frequently

ElementDescription: How often does anyone, including family and friends, scream or curse at you?
Notes: 1= Never; 2= Rarely; 3= Sometimes; 4= Fairly Often; 5= Frequently

ElementDescription: When you were a child, how hard was it for your family to pay for the very basics, like food, housing, medical care, and utilities?
Notes: 1= Very Hard; 2= Somewhat hard; 3= Not very hard

ElementDescription: Do you want help finding or keeping work or a job?
Notes: 1= Yes, help finding work; 2= Yes, help keeping work; 3= I do not need or want help

ElementDescription: If for any reason you need help with day-to-day activities such as bathing, preparing meals, shopping, managing finances, etc., do you get the help you need?
Notes: 1= I don't need any help; 2= I get all the help I need; 3= I could use a little more help; 4= I need a lot more help

ElementDescription: How often do you feel lonely or isolated from those around you?
Notes: 1= Never; 2= Rarely; 3= Sometimes; 4= Often; 5= Always

ElementDescription: Non-English language spoken at home
Notes: 0 = No; 1 = Yes

ElementDescription: Do you want help with school or training? For example, starting or completing job training or getting a high school diploma, GED or equivalent
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes

ElementDescription: In the last 30 days, other than the activities you did for work, on average, how many days per week did you engage in moderate exercise (like walking fast, running, jogging, dancing, swimming, biking, or other similar activities)?
On average, how many minutes did you usually spend exercising at this level on one of those days?

How many times in the past 12 months have you had 5 or more drinks in a day (males) or 4 or more drinks in a day (females)? One drink is 12 ounces of beer, 5 ounces of wine, or 1.5 ounces of 80-proof spirits.
Notes: 1= Never; 2= Once or twice; 3= Monthly; 4= Weekly; 5= Daily or almost daily

ElementDescription: How many times in the past 12 months have you used tobacco products (like cigarettes, cigars, snuff, chew, electronic cigarettes)?
Notes: 1= Never; 2= Once or twice; 3= Monthly; 4= Weekly; 5= Daily or almost daily

ElementDescription: How many times in the past year have you used prescription drugs for non-medical reasons?
Notes: 1= Never; 2= Once or twice; 3= Monthly; 4= Weekly; 5= Daily or almost daily

ElementDescription: How many times in the past year have you used illegal drugs?
Notes: 1= Never; 2= Once or twice; 3= Monthly; 4= Weekly; 5= Daily or almost daily

ElementDescription: Over the past 2 weeks, how often have you bothered by: Little interest or pleasure in doing things
Notes: 0=Not at all; 1=Several Days; 2=More than half the days; 3=Nearly every day; 888 = Don't know; 999 = Missing/Refuse

ElementDescription: Over the past 2 weeks, how often have you bothered by: Feeling down, depressed, irritable or hopeless
Notes: 0=Not at all; 1=Several Days; 2=More than half the days; 3=Nearly every day; 888 = Don't know; 999 = Missing/Refuse

ElementDescription: Stress means a situation in which a person feels tense, restless, nervous, or anxious, or is unable to sleep at night because his or her mind is troubled all the time. Do you feel this kind of stress these days?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little bit; 3= Somewhat; 4= Quite a bit; 5= ery much

ElementDescription: Because of a physical, mental, or emotional condition, do you have serious difficulty concentrating, remembering, or making decisions? (5 years old or older)
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes

ElementDescription: Because of a physical, mental, or emotional condition, do you have difficulty doing errands alone such as visiting a doctor's office or shopping? (15 years old or older)
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes

ElementDescription: How many times in the past year have you used Cannabis?
Notes: 1= Never; 2= Once or twice; 3= Monthly; 4= Weekly; 5= Daily or almost daily

ElementDescription: Within the past 12 months, you worried that your food would run out before you got money to buy more
Notes: 0 = Often true ; 1 = Sometimes true ; 2 = Never true

ElementDescription: Within the past 12 months, the food you bought just didn''t last and you didn''t have money to get more.
Notes: 0 = Often true ; 1 = Sometimes true ; 2 = Never true

ElementDescription: In the past 12 months, has lack of reliable transportation kept you from medical appointments, meetings, work or from getting things needed for daily living?
Notes: 1=It has kept me from medical appointments or getting medications; 2= It has kept me from non medical meetings, appointments, work, or getting things that I need; 3= It has not kept me from medical appointments, meetings work, or from getting things I need
